reviews.review_text:
As good as it gets. I don't think a better audience recording will emerge from this show.  Brilliant sound.  The band played strange, but that's not necessarily bad.  Famous show for good reason.


Thank you so much for uploading this source!  Let's get an equal or better source for 2.26.90, baby!

What a Find! Thanx M & K.  I had my most sinful dead weekend ever.  
Stayed in the same hotel as Phil on the beach in Monterey.  The first set is rather staid, though a nice jam at the end of Cassidy and a solid Deal close.
The second set is oh so good.  A great Rider from  a great Crazy Fingers.  The Playing gets wild with thrashing Brent, and a rare closing verse.  I've always favored this Playing with BCT 4/19/86 as I attended.  Drums/space are very psychotic for an outdoor show.  Gimme Some Lovin' thunders and this reading of Believe It or Not makes me wonder why this tune got left behind.  Too much potential.
I lost my decent sounding set II and set I was a huge upgrade for me.  So happy to hear this almost 20 years to the day.  I am opening my radio show with Cassidy through Drums this week.  Peace.

Cool show... ...with good sound.  All my friends got out to this one, but alas I could not.  Sorry to have missed it.

Believe it or Not is a cool tune...good late Jerry pathos.

Black Muddy River A great Black Muddy River, one of my favorites in fact.  A solid show worth the time to listen to, the China>Crazy Fingers>Rider is an interesting change of pace, very well played.

Also to note the Playin in the Band, a much hear for any Brent fans, its wonderful.

Overall I love this show, the whole thing.  I really like how strange 1988 sounds, and no its not just me I have heard this before.  Maybe it was something the band was into at the time a certain sound, but listen to 7/15, 7/16, and 7/17/88 for more examples of this "style" of dead.

I have heard others say they're "playing strange" but always in a good way. I read an interview once an Garcia had said the he was "just getting back to 100% after the coma" so maybe that's why.

Ahh, memories... A friend of mine "overnighted" me a copy of this tape the next day...  All the way from CA to FL...  I can remember us all listening to it, cross legged and dumbfounded with bongs in hand that they had somehow managed to squeeze Crazy Fingers in between China/Rider !  Seemed like the most amazing thing in the world at the time.  GOD, I miss those days !

Russ Cansler aud is better I listened to all 3 aud's and Russ Cansler has the best sound.
Try it yourself.  Don't change any levels or volume.  Just click on the same song and listen to it here and there.

Soooo Happy I was at this show, all three. having this brings back sooo many memories of and incredible 3 days. Friends good times and the memories. Thank you so much for posting. Ranks up there  Autzen for me
